==English==

=== Pronunciation ===
:səb-dŭk'shən

=== Etymology ===
:From Latin ''sub'' meaning under or below, and Latin ''ductum'' meaning to draw or conduct.

=== Noun ===
#'''Subduction''' is the condition of being pushed or drawn beneath another object.

=== Adjective ===
#(Geology) '''Subduction zone''' is a place where one [[tectonics|tectonic]] [[plate]] is being pushed underneath another plate.